        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "feat(ui): auto-title dashboard sessions from first user message",
        "body": "## What Problem This Solves\n\nControl UI dashboard sessions created via **New session** show raw session keys (for example `agent:main:dashboard:<uuid>`) in the sidebar until manually renamed. This makes recent-session navigation hard to scan.\n\n## Why This Change Was Made\n\n- Show a localized **New Session** fallback immediately for unlabeled dashboard sessions.\n- After the first user message in a dashboard session, generate a short title via the existing `generateConversationLabel()` helper and persist it as `entry.label`.\n- Broadcast `sessions.changed` so the sidebar updates without a manual refresh.\n\n## User Impact\n\n- Sidebar recent sessions and the session switcher show **New Session** / **新会话** instead of UUID keys for new dashboard chats.\n- The title updates once after the first message and stays fixed unless the user renames the session.\n\n## Evidence\n\n- `pnpm test src/gateway/dashboard-session-auto-label.test.ts ui/src/ui/app-render.helpers.node.test.ts`\n- `pnpm build`\n- Local dev verified with `pnpm ui:dev` + `pnpm gateway:watch:raw`\n\n\nMade with [Cursor](https://cursor.com)",
        "branch": "sunq/feat-dashboard-session-auto-title",
